    <section name="JMX Integration">
      <p>
        Dozer can be managed via JMX. The Dozer distibution contains fully functional JMX MBeans.  
        These MBeans can be found in the net.sf.dozer.util.mapping.jmx package.  To hook into these MBeans,
        the system using Dozer will just need to register these MBeans with the appropriate JMX server.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Dozer JMX MBeans</b>
      </p>
      <table border="1">
        <tr>
          <th>MBean</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>DozerStatisticsControllerMBean</td>
          <td>Runtime mapping statistics.  The <a href="./configuration/statistics.html">Statistics</a> 
          section contains more information on the types of statistics that are available.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>DozerAdminControllerMBean</td>
          <td>Admin functions</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
